President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. John P. Bilbrey, the President and CEO of The Hershey Company, will be appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations. Brian Greenspun, owner of the Greenspun Media Group, will be appointed as a member of the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad. Andrés W. López, an attorney and founder of The Law Offices of Andrés W. López, P.S.C., will be appointed as a General Trustee on the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Emma Sepulveda, a Foundation Professor at the University of Nevada, Reno, will be appointed as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. President Obama expressed his pleasure in appointing these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the future.